        <record id="action_records_container" model="ir.actions.act_window">
            <!-- OPTIMIZATION: Model records.container has state field - consider using default search filters -->
            <field name="name">Storage Containers</field>
            <field name="res_model">records.container</field>
            <field name="view_mode">list,kanban,form,calendar,graph</field>
            <field name="context">{
            'search_default_stored': 1,
            'search_default_active': 1
        }</field>
            <field name="help" type="html">
                <p class="o_view_nocontent_smiling_face">
                    <i class="fa fa-cube"/> No storage containers yet!
                </p>
                <p>
                    <b>‚ö†Ô∏è Before creating containers, ensure you have configured:</b>
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>‚úì <b>Storage Locations</b> - Go to: <i>Configuration &gt; Master Data &gt; Storage Locations</i></li>
                    <li>‚úì <b>Container Types</b> - Go to: <i>Configuration &gt; Products &amp; Services &gt; Service Products</i></li>
                    <li>‚úì <b>Customer &amp; Department</b> - Go to: <i>Contacts &gt; Create Company</i> (check "Is a Records Management Customer")</li>
                    <li>‚úì <b>Barcode Sequences</b> - Go to: <i>Configuration &gt; Barcode Configuration</i> (auto-created on first use)</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    <b>üìã To create your first container:</b>
                </p>
                <ol>
                    <li>Click the <b>New</b> button above</li>
                    <li>Select a <b>Customer</b> and <b>Department</b></li>
                    <li>Choose a <b>Container Type</b> (e.g., "Bankers Box 15x12x10")</li>
                    <li>Assign a <b>Storage Location</b> (e.g., "Warehouse A &gt; Section A1 &gt; Spot A1-001")</li>
                    <li>Click <b>Save</b> - barcode will auto-generate</li>
                    <li>Use <b>Generate QR Code</b> or <b>Generate Barcode</b> buttons to print labels</li>
                </ol>
                <p>
                    <b>üöÄ Key Features:</b><br/>
                    ‚Ä¢ Visual kanban boards for container tracking<br/>
                    ‚Ä¢ Automated barcode and QR code generation<br/>
                    ‚Ä¢ Real-time location tracking with movement history<br/>
                    ‚Ä¢ Document association and content management<br/>
                    ‚Ä¢ Mobile-optimized for warehouse operations
                </p>
                <p>
                    <b>üí° Quick Tip:</b> Use filters to view containers by status (Stored, Indexed, Retrieved, Destroyed)
                </p>
            </field>
        </record>
